TeaCozy Website
A stylish and responsive website for a fictional tea shop called TeaCozy. This project demonstrates the use of modern web design principles, including HTML5, CSS3, and responsive design techniques.

Project Overview
TeaCozy is a minimalist website built to practice and showcase front-end development skills. It features a sleek layout with sections for the shop's mission, locations, and menu, providing an excellent example of structuring and styling content effectively.

Features
  Responsive Design: Optimized for various screen sizes, ensuring a seamless user experience across desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.
  Multi-Section Layout:
  Header: A clean navigation bar with links to each section of the site.
  Mission Statement: Highlights the shop's dedication to quality tea.
  Locations Section: Displays store locations in a grid layout with relevant details.
  Menu Section: Lists various tea offerings with an elegant presentation.
  CSS Styling: Carefully crafted styles using flexbox for layout and modern design aesthetics.

Technologies Used
  HTML5: For semantic and structured content.
  CSS3: To create a visually appealing and responsive layout.
  Flexbox: For flexible and efficient layout management.
